public interface ApplicationGroupBuilder<A extends Application<A>,S extends ApplicationSchema<A,S>,B extends ApplicationBuilder<A,S>,G extends ApplicationGroup<A>>

An ApplicationGroupBuilder is a builder for ApplicationGroups. That is, collections of related Applications.

Author:
Brian Oliver

Method Detail

addBuilder

void addBuilder(B builder,
                S schema,
                String sPrefix,
                int cRequiredInstances)
Adds a ApplicationBuilder to the ApplicationGroupBuilder that will be used to realize a type of Application when the ApplicationGroup is realized with realize(ApplicationConsole).

Parameters:
builder - the ApplicationBuilder for the Applications
schema - the ApplicationSchema from which to realize/configure the Applications
sPrefix - the Application name prefix for each of the realized Application
cRequiredInstances - the number of instances of the Application that should be realized for the ApplicationGroup when realize(ApplicationConsole) is called

realize

G realize(ApplicationConsole console)
                                      throws IOException
Realizes an instance of an ApplicationGroup.

Parameters:
console - The ApplicationConsole that will be used for I/O by the Applications realized in the ApplicationGroup. This may be null if not required.
Returns:
An ApplicationGroup representing the collection of realized Applications.
Throws:
IOException - Thrown if a problem occurs while realizing the application
